The article announces the continuation of the national emergency with respect to the situation in Zimbabwe. It explains that the President declared a national emergency in 2003 due to the actions and policies of certain members of the Government of Zimbabwe and other individuals undermining democratic processes or institutions. The article also mentions that additional steps were taken in 2005 and 2008 to address the emergency. The President states that the actions and policies of these individuals still pose a threat to the foreign policy of the United States, and therefore, the national emergency must continue beyond March 6, 2012. The notice concludes by stating that the continuation of the national emergency will be transmitted to Congress.